Datashaman\\Logic.name: Datashaman\Logic\D

Creates a function that calls a function on a Just (it should return the value)
and returns a default on a Nothing value.

Datashaman\\Logic.name: Datashaman\Logic\I
Datashaman\\Logic.summary: Creates an identity function (returns its value unchanged).

Datashaman\\Logic.name: Datashaman\Logic\J
Datashaman\\Logic.summary: Creates a function which wraps a value with Just.

Datashaman\\Logic.name: Datashaman\Logic\N
Datashaman\\Logic.summary: Creates a function which returns Nothing

Datashaman\\Logic.name: Datashaman\Logic\V
Datashaman\\Logic.summary: Creates a function which returns the unwrapped monad value.

Datashaman\\Logic.name: Datashaman\Logic\K
Datashaman\\Logic.summary: Creates a constant function (returns the same value regardless of argument).

Datashaman\\Logic.name: Datashaman\Logic\P
Datashaman\\Logic.summary: An alias for creating predicate functions.

Datashaman\\Logic.name: Datashaman\Logic\S
Datashaman\\Logic.summary: Application (not sure what to do with this yet)

Datashaman\\Logic.name: Datashaman\Logic\M
Datashaman\\Logic.summary: Creates a match function which takes one parameter (the subject):

Datashaman\\Logic.name: Datashaman\Logic\T
Datashaman\\Logic.summary: Create a function that always returns true

Datashaman\\Logic.name: Datashaman\Logic\F
Datashaman\\Logic.summary: Create a function that always returns false

Datashaman\\Logic.name: Datashaman\Logic\Do_
Datashaman\\Logic.summary: Resolve a chain of monadic values into a context and call a result function with that context.

Datashaman\\Logic.name: Datashaman\Logic\curry
Datashaman\\Logic.summary: Curry a callable.

parameters.description: local arguments defined while the expression is evaluated

Datashaman\\Logic.name: Datashaman\Logic\repr

parameters.name: value
parameters.description: the value to represent

Datashaman\\Logic.summary: Return a simple string representation of the value for display and logging.

Datashaman\\Logic.name: Datashaman\Logic\either
Datashaman\\Logic.summary: If the either monad is a Left, call the first callable with the monad value.

Datashaman\\Logic.name: Datashaman\Logic\mkLeft
Datashaman\\Logic.summary: Make a Left value. If no arguments are supplied, return a function which creates Left values.

Datashaman\\Logic.name: Datashaman\Logic\mkRight
Datashaman\\Logic.summary: Make a Right value. If no arguments are supplied, return a function which creates Right values.

Datashaman\\Logic.name: Datashaman\Logic\fromLeft
Datashaman\\Logic.summary: Return a Left value or a default if not Left.

Datashaman\\Logic.name: Datashaman\Logic\fromRight
Datashaman\\Logic.summary: Return a Right value or a default if not Right.

Datashaman\\Logic.name: Datashaman\Logic\isLeft
Datashaman\\Logic.summary: Is an either value a Left value.

Datashaman\\Logic.name: Datashaman\Logic\isRight
Datashaman\\Logic.summary: Is an either value a Right value.

Datashaman\\Logic.name: Datashaman\Logic\lefts
Datashaman\\Logic.summary: Return a List_ of the lefts in a list of eithers.

Datashaman\\Logic.name: Datashaman\Logic\rights
Datashaman\\Logic.summary: Return a List_ of the rights in a list of eithers.

Datashaman\\Logic.name: Datashaman\Logic\fromJust
Datashaman\\Logic.summary: The fromJust function extracts the element out of a Just and throws an error if its argument is Nothing.

Datashaman\\Logic.name: Datashaman\Logic\fromMaybe
Datashaman\\Logic.summary: The fromMaybe function takes a default value and and Maybe value. If the Maybe is Nothing, it returns the default values; otherwise, it returns the value contained in the Maybe.

Datashaman\\Logic.name: Datashaman\Logic\catMaybes
Datashaman\\Logic.summary: The catMaybes function takes a list of Maybes and returns a List_ of all the Just values.
